    "Proof of Theorem 4.3: We follow the general proof scheme for PAC-Bayes bounds, with some important differences.",
    "Fist, Hoeffding's inequality will be replaced by Bernstein's inequality.",
    "But another very important point is to use the inequality on the \"relative losses\" ℓ i (θ *) -ℓ i (θ) instead of the loss ℓ i (θ) (for this reason, excess risk bounds are also sometimes called \"relative bounds\").",
    "This is to ensure that we can use Bernstein condition.",
    "So, let us fix θ ∈ Θ and apply Lemma 3.8 to"
  ]
